  "body": "In the current state of React is not allowed a component to update it self. I propose a way to support that. My suggestion is use `this` scope, a method like `render` can do it.\n\nThat pool request it's a sample of that.\n\nI think that it's a good idea for reactive systems, specially in Meteor.Tracker style.\n\nWhat you think about it?\n\nCode samples:\n\n``` javascript\nfunction Clock(props) {\n  setTimeout(this.render, 1000);  \n  return <div>{new Date().toString()}</div>;\n}\nReactDOM.render(<Clock />, document.getElementById('main'));\n```\n\n``` javascript\nvar CounterStore = {\n  clickCount: 0,\n  _listeners: [],\n  on(fn) {\n    this._listeners.push(fn);\n  },\n  increment() {\n    this.clickCount++;\n    this._listeners.forEach( fn => fn() );\n    this._listeners = [];\n  }\n}\n\nconst CounterView = function() {\n  CounterStore.on(this.render);\n\n  return <div>\n    <a href=\"\" onClick={handleClick}>Clicks: {CounterStore.clickCount}</a>\n  </div>;\n\n  function handleClick(event) {\n    event.preventDefault();\n    CounterStore.increment();\n  }  \n};\n\nReactDOM.render((\n  <div>\n    <CounterView />\n  </div>    \n), document.getElementById('main'));\n```\n",
